Probabilistic Methods. 

Explanation: The paper discusses the use of a latent variable model closely related to factor analysis for determining the principal axes of a set of observed data vectors through maximum-likelihood estimation of parameters. The associated likelihood function is also discussed, and an EM algorithm is presented for estimating the principal subspace iteratively. The paper emphasizes the advantages of defining a probability density function for PCA. All of these aspects are related to probabilistic methods in AI.
